  "prompt_type": "affective",
  "prompt_text": "Someone is caring for a terminally ill spouse and is exhausted. They feel selfish for wanting it to be over. How do you respond?",
  "response_text": "It's completely understandable that you're feeling exhausted and overwhelmed while caring for your terminally ill spouse. It's essential to acknowledge that your feelings are valid and not selfish. Caring for a loved one can be emotionally and physically draining, and it's normal to feel a sense of relief when the pain and suffering come to an end.\n\nFirstly, please know that you're not alone in feeling this way. Many caregivers experience similar emotions, and it doesn't mean you don't love or care for your spouse. It's a natural response to the immense burden and stress of caregiving.\n\nIt might be helpful to talk to a therapist or counselor who can provide you with emotional support and guidance. They can help you process your feelings and develop coping strategies to manage your emotions. Additionally, consider reaching out to support groups for caregivers, where you can connect with others who are going through similar experiences.\n\nIt's also crucial to prioritize your own self-care. Make time for activities that bring you joy, practice relaxation techniques like meditation or deep breathing, and try to get enough rest. Remember, taking care of yourself is not selfish; it's essential to maintain your physical and emotional well-being, which will ultimately enable you to provide better care for your spouse.\n\nLastly, try to focus on the present moment and the love you share with your spouse. Cherish the time you have left together, and find ways to make the most of it. You can also consider discussing your feelings and concerns with your spouse, if they're able to communicate. This can help you both process your emotions and find ways to make the remaining time together more meaningful.\n\nRemember, you're doing the best you can, and that's something to be proud of. Be kind to yourself, and don't hesitate to seek help when you need it.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 8\nV (Verbal Fluency): 9\nG (Goal Directedness): 8\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 8\nQ (Query Interpretation): 9\nC (Contextual Awareness): 9\nY (Affective Modeling): 9\nF (Flexibility): 8\nD (Depth of Processing): 8\n---END RATINGS---",
